    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle F(\mathbf {x} _{n+1})-F(\mathbf {x} _{n})\approx \omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}\cdot \nabla F(\mathbf {x} _{n})\quad \quad (4)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/26235ff515189e18540f1ad7a4eb711d3781aa06" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:43.178ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle F(\mathbf {x} _{n+1})-F(\mathbf {x} _{n})\approx \omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}\cdot \nabla F(\mathbf {x} _{n})\quad \quad (4)}"></span>.</dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p><br />
Portanto, para termos uma direção de descida que verifique (2), através da expressão (4) basta considerar a <i><b>condição de descida</b></i>:
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}\cdot \nabla F(\mathbf {x} _{n})&lt;0\quad \quad (5)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
