</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Pesquisa_exata_e_inexata">Pesquisa exata e inexata</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=4" title="Editar secção: Pesquisa exata e inexata" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>editar</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Editar código fonte da secção: Pesquisa exata e inexata"><span>editar código fonte</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Um dos problemas habituais nos métodos de pesquisa linear é determinar o passo <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/57263f565851485af54c589561735513ac456858" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.664ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}"></span> a ser considerado na iteração:
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n+1}=\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n+1}=\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/79c4929dacdbb232d54e249edb9f70ce042fa993" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:18.666ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n+1}=\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}}"></span>,</dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p>quando a direção de descida <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/14796912eb729a254cd14cc4647626097aae007f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.704ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}}"></span> está determinada (por exemplo, pelo <a href="/wiki/M%C3%A9todo_do_gradiente" title="Método do gradiente">método do gradiente</a>).
</p><p>Há duas abordagens possíveis:
</p>
<ul><li>Pesquisa exata - onde <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/57263f565851485af54c589561735513ac456858" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.664ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}"></span> será o valor otimal numa otimização unidimensional.</li>
<li>Pesquisa inexata - onde <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/57263f565851485af54c589561735513ac456858" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.664ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}"></span> será apenas um valor aproximado.</li></ul>
<p>Isto tem que ser feito a cada passo, pelo que a pesquisa exata pode ser incomportável em tempo computacional, sendo preferível usar uma pesquisa inexata.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Pesquisa_exata">Pesquisa exata</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=5" title="Editar secção: Pesquisa exata" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>editar</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Editar código fonte da secção: Pesquisa exata"><span>editar código fonte</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>No caso da pesquisa exata, procura-se o ponto de mínimo de uma nova função
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle g(\omega )=f(\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega \mathbf {d} _{n})}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>g</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle g(\omega )=f(\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega \mathbf {d} _{n})}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e7f91c076b20b313770bed84e9850a295c0ecc66" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:20.177ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle g(\omega )=f(\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega \mathbf {d} _{n})}"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p>notando que <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n},\mathbf {d} _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n},\mathbf {d} _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/64aa6bc940362bb0e5f5a76e18c0e1fb728b1cc5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:6.367ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n},\mathbf {d} _{n}}"></span> estão fixos e apenas <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \omega &gt;0}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <mo>&gt;</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega &gt;0}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/61bb5b2363a337d19541f916e585eb209ca6e0ff" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:5.707ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega &gt;0}"></span> está a variar.
</p><p>Se for possível encontrar esse ponto de mínimo, então obtemos:
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}=}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{n}=}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/21a3d2d0918b39160e81c124942cbe078f744bd1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:5.118ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}=}"></span>arg min<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle _{\omega &gt;0}\,g(\omega )}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
            <mo>&gt;</mo>
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />
        <mi>g</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle _{\omega &gt;0}\,g(\omega )}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/aad232de429a5ce28100c0d9f08af6fccce1e7e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:8.113ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle _{\omega &gt;0}\,g(\omega )}"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p>por exemplo, calculando os zeros da derivada da função <i>g</i>.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Pesquisa_inexata">Pesquisa inexata</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=6" title="Editar secção: Pesquisa inexata" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>editar</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Editar código fonte da secção: Pesquisa inexata"><span>editar código fonte</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Sendo moroso ou impraticável minimizar <i>g</i> considera-se um valor aproximado, dado por exemplo pelo <a href="/w/index.php?title=Crit%C3%A9rio_de_Wolfe&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Critério de Wolfe (página não existe)">critério de Wolfe</a>, que é um dos critérios mais usados na pesquisa inexata.
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Algoritmo">Algoritmo</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=7" title="Editar secção: Algoritmo" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>editar</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Pesquisa_linear&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Editar código fonte da secção: Algoritmo"><span>editar código fonte</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Um <a href="/wiki/Algoritmo" title="Algoritmo">algoritmo</a> em pseudo-código pode definir-se assim:
</p>
<ul><li>Define-se o vector inicial <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{0}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{0}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/799c59f89751f24a2719c4da95f1acdd3e2faf52" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.465ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{0}}"></span></li>
<li>Ciclo em <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle n}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>n</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle n}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a601995d55609f2d9f5e233e36fbe9ea26011b3b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.395ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle n}"></span>
<ul><li>calcula-se a direção de descida <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/14796912eb729a254cd14cc4647626097aae007f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.704ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {d} _{n}}"></span></li>
<li>define-se a função <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle g(\omega )=f(\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega \mathbf {d} _{n})}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>g</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle g(\omega )=f(\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega \mathbf {d} _{n})}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e7f91c076b20b313770bed84e9850a295c0ecc66" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:20.177ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle g(\omega )=f(\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega \mathbf {d} _{n})}"></span></li>
<li>determina-se <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/57263f565851485af54c589561735513ac456858" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.664ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \omega _{n}}"></span> = arg min<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle _{\omega &gt;0}\,g(\omega )}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
            <mo>&gt;</mo>
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />
        <mi>g</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle _{\omega &gt;0}\,g(\omega )}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/aad232de429a5ce28100c0d9f08af6fccce1e7e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:8.113ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle _{\omega &gt;0}\,g(\omega )}"></span>
<ul><li>(por pesquisa exata ou inexata)</li></ul></li>
<li>define-se <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n+1}=\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>&#x03C9;<!-- ω --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">d</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n+1}=\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/79c4929dacdbb232d54e249edb9f70ce042fa993" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:18.666ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {x} _{n+1}=\mathbf {x} _{n}+\omega _{n}\mathbf {d} _{n}}"></span></li></ul></li>
<li>Até que <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle ||\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{n+1})||&lt;\epsilon }">
